As a build up to its numerous developmental projects, Entertainment Media and Events Promoters Association of Nigeria (EMEPAN) is set to organise a free masterclass/workshop on events reportage and management for young industry practitioners. The workshop, which holds on August 2, 2022 at CCX Premium Bar and Event Center, 273, Kofo Abayomi Street, Victoria Island, Lagos, would feature reputable industry players as resource persons and they will share their wealth of experience and ideas with the passion-driven youths. According to EMEPAN’s director of communications, Amaobi Madu, the founding members and team members have been working behind the scene over the years and have decided to officially unveil its visions and programmes to the public. “The workshop will be an opportunity for the youths, who are new entrants in the sector, to have a session with the industry eggheads, and this will inspire and motivate them to exhibit professionalism while rendering their services to society,” he said. EMEPAN was registered in 2017, with seasoned journalist and Group Political Editor, Thisday newspaper, Nseobong Okon-Ekong and vice chairman, Nigeria Bar Association (NBA), Lagos State chapter, Okey Ilofulunwa as founding members, alongside other notable industry players